      <hedline>
        <hl1>Camden to Enforce Curfew</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By TERRY PRISTIN</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">PRISTIN, TERRY</byline>
      <dateline>CAMDEN</dateline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>For about four decades, Camden's curfew for residents under 18 has largely been ignored. Now, city officials hope that enforcing the curfew between 10 P.M. and 6 A.M. on weekdays (with an 11 P.M. start on weekends) will help them cut down on juvenile crime.</p>
        <p>To alert young people that the curfew has begun, a siren on top of City Hall has been activated for the first time in 25 years, Police Chief Bob Pugh said yesterday. Violating the curfew can lead to a $1,000 fine imposed against parents, The Associated Press reported.</p>
      </block>
